import React from "react"; export default function ToolInspectionTable() { const checklist = [ "Tool is clean and free from debris", "No cracks, damage, or wear on handles/grips", "Blades/cutting edges are sharp and undamaged (if applicable)", "Power cord is intact (no cuts, exposed wires)", "Plug is undamaged and securely attached", "Safety guards/shields are in place and functional", "Switches and controls work correctly", "Tool operates properly during test (if applicable)", "Battery or power supply functions correctly (if applicable)", "Tool stored safely after inspection", ]; return (
{checklist.map((item, index) => ( ))}
# Item to Check ✔ ✘ Comments/Action Needed
{index + 1} {item}
); }
